// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p01/pass.test — P1 line-orientation per
// `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` §2 + the "Validation tests" topic table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`.
//
// Topic per `tasks.md` T037: "directive at column 0 succeeds; an
// indented `#define` is treated as a passthrough line per P1 (no P1
// fail-case is meaningful since 'indented #' is intentionally not a
// directive — the passing fixture asserts the indented case produces
// NO macro definition)".
//
// What this fixture asserts:
//   * A column-0 `#define X 1` on line 1 is consumed by the
//     preprocessor (P1) — no tokens for it cross the seam (P12).
//   * `%X%` on the passthrough line uses the macro and splices to
//     `1`.
//   * An indented `  #define Y 2` is NOT a directive (P1 narrower-
//     than-C semantics): no Y macro is defined, so a subsequent
//     `%Y%` would be an undefined-macro error (we only assert the
//     positive shape here — see p03/fail.test for the undef-macro
//     diagnostic).
//
// **Implementation state**: this fixture runs RED against the
// unchanged Phase-3 tree because no preprocessor exists — the lexer
// sees the literal `#define X 1` and tokenizes it as
// `tk_hash_sign_extend` + `tk_identifier`/`tk_decimal_lit` rather
// than consuming it. Phase-4 (lib/Preprocess/) turns it green.

// RUN: echo '#define X 1' >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg x = %%X%%;' >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// The column-0 #define is consumed (no tokens emitted for line 1).
// The use site `%X%` splices to `1`; the surrounding tokens are the
// regular `reg`/`x`/`=`/<int>/`;`.
//
// We do NOT anchor on absolute coordinates here because the macro
// substitution may render the value into the passthrough line at
// different physical positions depending on implementation detail
// (textual splice vs. value substitution); we only assert kind +
// spelling.
// CHECK:      tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}x
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_assign{{[ \t]+}}=
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_decimal_lit{{[ \t]+}}1
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_semicolon{{[ \t]+}};
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_eof

// And the column-0 #define MUST NOT cross the P12 seam:
// CHECK-NOT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}define
